{
    "Description": "<h3>Usage</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">net.smtp.sendEmail{\n    server=&lt;value&gt;,\n    to=&lt;value&gt;,\n    from=&lt;value&gt;,\n    header=&lt;value&gt;,\n    body=&lt;value&gt;,\n    ...\n}\n</pre><ul><li><code><strong>server</strong></code>: The server the email will be sent through.</li><li><code><strong>to</strong></code>: An array of recipient emails.</li><li><code><strong>from</strong></code>: The sender's email address.</li><li><code><strong>header</strong></code>: A table of key value pairs representing the header fields.</li><li><code><strong>body</strong></code>: The body of the email.</li><li>Most users only need to specify <code><strong>server</strong></code>, <code><strong>to</strong></code>, <code><strong>from</strong></code>, <code><strong>header</strong></code>, <code><strong>body</strong></code>. Additional optional parameters like <code><strong>use_ssl</strong></code> can be used to fine-tune the connection if needed. They are detailed below the Example section.</li></ul><p><br></p><h3>Notes</h3><ul><li>Sends an email using the SMTP protocol. </li><li>The header fields are for <em>display only</em>, the \"To\" param contains the actual email recipient(s). Therefore to do <strong>Bcc</strong> you just add the recipient address in the \"To\" param.</li><li>Some common header fields include: </li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>From:</code> (mandatory)</li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>To:</code></li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>Subject:</code></li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>Date:</code> (mandatory)</li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>Message-ID:</code></li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>Bcc:</code></li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>Cc:</code></li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>Content-Type:</code> (non-standard)</li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>In-Reply-To:</code></li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>Precedence:</code> (non-standard)</li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>Received:</code></li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>References:</code></li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>Reply-To:</code></li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>Sender:</code></li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>Return-Path:</code></li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>Errors-To:</code> (non-standard)</li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>X-*</code> (recommended for custom fields)</li><li>Though <code>X-*</code> is recommended for custom header fields, in fact, any header not expressly defined in the RFC, is allowed, and ignored by most e-mail systems. For example there are three (common) non-standard fields in the list above: </li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>Content-Type:</code></li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>Precedence:</code></li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>Errors-To:</code></li></ul><p><br></p><h3><strong>Example</strong></h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">local Header = {To = 'adam@smith.com'; -- bcc to jane@smith.com \n   From = 'will@smith.com';            -- show a different name as sender\n   Date = 'Thu, 23 Aug 2001 21:27:04 -0400';\n   Subject = 'Test Subject';\n}\n\nnet.smtp.sendEmail{\n   server='smtp://mysmtp.com:25', \n   username='john', password='password',\n   from='john@smith.com',\n   to={'adam@smith.com', 'jane@smith.com'},\n   header=Header, \n   body='Test Email Body', \n   use_ssl='try'\n }\n</pre><h3><br></h3><h3>Other Supported Options</h3><p>The options listed below are all optional.</p><h4>Connection Behaviour Options</h4><ul><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>username</strong></code>: Username to use. If this and password are empty or not specified, no authentication will be used.</li><li><code><strong>password</strong></code>: Password to use. If this and username are empty or not specified, no authentication will be used.</li><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>timeout</strong></code>: Timeout in seconds for the send operation.</li><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>live</strong></code>: If <code>true</code>, allows for sending emails while in translator.</li><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>debug</strong></code>: <em> </em>If <code>true</code>, returns verbose debug information - errors thrown will also contain debug information.</li></ul><p><br></p><h4>Ssl Related Options:</h4><ul><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>use_ssl</strong></code>: Enable explicit SSL mode. Valid options: <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">all</code> (always enable), <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">try</code> (optional), <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">control</code> (control connection) (default is <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">try</code>)</li><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>certificate_file</strong></code>: The name of your certificate file.</li><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>certificate_type</strong></code>: The type of the certificate file, either <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">PEM</code> (default) or <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">DER</code>.</li><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>private_key_file</strong></code>: The name of your private key file.</li><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>private_key_pass</strong></code>: The password to your private key file.</li><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>private_key_type</strong></code>: Your private key's type either <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">PEM</code> (default), <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">DER</code>, or <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">ENG</code>.</li><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>ssl_engine</strong></code>: The engine to use when <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>private_key_type</strong></code> is set to <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">ENG</code>. This applies when the key is managed by a cryptographic engine.</li><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>verify_peer</strong></code>: If <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">true</code>, verify the peer's certificate</li><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>verify_host</strong></code>: If <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">true</code>, verify the host's certificate matches URL</li><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>ca_file</strong></code>: The certificate(s) file to use for peer verification.</li><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>issuer_cert</strong></code>: The PEM certificate file to validate the issuer of the peer's certificate during peer validation.</li><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>crl_file</strong></code>: The name of the certificate revocation list to use during peer validation.</li><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>ssl_version</strong></code>: Use a particular SSL version(s).</li><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>cipher_list</strong></code>: Provide a list of ciphers in OpenSSL format to use. Use <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>cipher_suite_list</strong></code> to set ciphers for TLSv1.3.</li><li><code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\"><strong>cipher_suite_list</strong></code>: Provide a list of TLSv1.3 cipher suites in OpenSSL format to use.</li></ul>",
    "Name": "net.smtp.sendEmail",
    "Parameters": [
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>string</u> </em>The server the email will be sent through.</p>",
            "Name": "server",
            "Required": true
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>table</u></em> Recipient emails, an array containing a list of strings, each of the form 'email@domain.com'.</p>",
            "Name": "to",
            "Required": true
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>string</u> </em>Sender email address, e.g., 'user@host.com'.</p>",
            "Name": "from",
            "Required": true
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>table</u> </em>A table of key value pairs representing the header.</p>",
            "Name": "header",
            "Required": true
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>string</u> </em>A string containing the body of the message.</p>",
            "Name": "body",
            "Required": true
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>string</u> </em>Username to use. If this and password are empty or not specified, no authentication will be used.</p>",
            "Name": "username",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>string</u> </em>Password to use. If this and username are empty or not specified, no authentication will be used.</p>",
            "Name": "password",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>integer</u> </em>Timeout for the send (default = <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">15</code> seconds).</p>",
            "Name": "timeout",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>string</u> </em>Options are: <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">yes</code> - SSL will be used or an error will occur; <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">no</code> - SSL will not be used; or <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">try</code> - SSL will be used if possible (default = <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">no</code>).</p>",
            "Name": "use_ssl",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>string</u> </em>The name of your certificate file.</p>",
            "Name": "certificate_file",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>string</u> </em>Your certificate's type: <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">PEM</code> (default) or <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">DER</code>.</p>",
            "Name": "certificate_type",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>string</u> </em>The name of your private key file.</p>",
            "Name": "private_key_file",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>string</u> </em>The password to access your private key.</p>",
            "Name": "private_key_pass",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>string</u> </em>Your private key's type: <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">PEM</code> (default), <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">DER</code>, or <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">ENG</code>.</p>",
            "Name": "private_key_type",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>string</u> </em>The engine to use with 'key_type' ENG.</p>",
            "Name": "ssl_engine",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>bool</u> </em>Verify peer certificate (default is <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">true</code>).</p>",
            "Name": "verify_peer",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>bool</u> </em>Verify host certificate matches URL (default is <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">true</code>).</p>",
            "Name": "verify_host",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>string</u> </em>The certificate(s) file to use for peer verification.</p>",
            "Name": "ca_file",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>string</u> </em>The PEM certificate file to validate the issuer of the peer's certificate during peer validation.</p>",
            "Name": "issuer_cert",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>string</u> </em>The name of the certificate revocation list to use during peer validation.</p>",
            "Name": "crl_file",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>string</u> </em>use a particular SSL version(s). Possible values for ssl_version are tls-v1, tls-v1.1, tls-v1.2, tls-v1.3. The default behavior is to try tls-v1.3 and then tls-v1.2. Specifying tls-v1 will allow connections to use all tls versions (starting with tls-v1.3 down to tls-v1.0).</p>",
            "Name": "ssl_version",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>string</u> </em>Provide a list of ciphers in OpenSSL format to use. Use cipher_suite_list to set ciphers for TLSv1.3.</p>",
            "Name": "cipher_list",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>string</u> </em>Provide a list of TLSv1.3 cipher suites in OpenSSL format to use.</p>",
            "Name": "cipher_suite_list",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>bool</u> </em>When true, emails will be sent while in the editor (default is <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">false</code>).</p>",
            "Name": "live",
            "Required": false
        },
        {
            "Description": "<p><em><u>bool</u> </em>When true return verbose debug information - errors thrown will also contain debug information (default is <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">false</code>).</p>",
            "Name": "debug",
            "Required": false
        }
    ],
    "ParameterTable": true,
    "SummaryLine": "Sends an email using the SMTP protocol."
}